cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques for relation extraction. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and long short-term memory (LSTM) architectures for learning word vector representations from character embeddings suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks for relation extraction and the incorporation of word embeddings suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The task of extracting relationships between chemicals and diseases suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of state-of-the-art approaches for relation extraction suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
